<div id="review_1611570235" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1611570235" />
    <a title="Cale" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9981339-cale"><img alt="Cale" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1338789060p2/9981339.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1611570235?book_show_action=true">Apr 15, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cale" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cale" href="/user/show/9981339-cale">Cale</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1611570235" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7333101111717951508">&quot;Twisting My Kaleidoscope” is a (90%) true story and an exceptional reading experience. The narrative is concise, direct and honest, and moves along quickly. The author Shannon Love takes us on her journey that spans over different periods of her life and her various struggles with mental illness, and huge obstacles she’s had to overcome in her treatment and her recovery. For anyone who may be going through rough periods in their lives, this story will give courage and strength. An inspiring and</span>
  <span id="freeText7333101111717951508" style="display:none">"Twisting My Kaleidoscope” is a (90%) true story and an exceptional reading experience. The narrative is concise, direct and honest, and moves along quickly. The author Shannon Love takes us on her journey that spans over different periods of her life and her various struggles with mental illness, and huge obstacles she’s had to overcome in her treatment and her recovery. For anyone who may be going through rough periods in their lives, this story will give courage and strength. An inspiring and fascinating read well worth the time. This is the first nonfiction book that I’ve read on this particular subject (a woman who suffers from mental psychosis), even though I am a big fan of memoirs and the whole “personal struggle” element. What spoke to me most about this book was just the face that despite everything else, at the heart of it this is a love story with herself and with her family and her God…one that is tested over and over, and we really feel the struggle the author goes through. So many ups and downs we feel like we are on a roller coaster. A great addition to the self-help genre, or for anyone who just wants an inspiring story. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7333101111717951508" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


